- VSCode Version: 1.3.0-insider; commit  a6aa320 
- OS Version: Windows 8

Issues:
1. empty-range after-content-text does not appear at the beginning of lines
2. empty-range before-content-text does not appear at the end of lines
3. neither before- nor after-content can appear on empty lines

see: #7181

MWE:

``` typescript
  const decBefore = vscode.window.createTextEditorDecorationType({
    before: { contentText: "$BEFORE-CONTENT$" }
  });
  const decAfter = vscode.window.createTextEditorDecorationType({
    after: { contentText: "$AFTER-CONTENT$" }
  });
  const editor = vscode.window.activeTextEditor;
  if (editor) {
    const lines = [
      "after-content at the beginning of this line (does not appear; bug)",
      "after-content at end of this line (ok)",
      "after-content on an empty line (does not appear; bug):",
      "",
      "before-content at beginning of this line (ok)",
      "before-content at end of this line (does not appear; bug)",
      "before-content on an empty line (does not appear; bug):",
      "", "END OF EXAMPLE", "" ]
    editor.edit((edit) => {
      edit.insert(new vscode.Position(0,0), lines.join('\n'));
    }).then(() => {
      // Note the empty ranges
      // after-content appears at the second range but not the first or third
      editor.setDecorations(decAfter, [new vscode.Range(0,0,0,0), new vscode.Range(1,lines[1].length,1,lines[1].length), new vscode.Range(3,0,3,0)]);
      // before-content appears at the first range but not the second or third
      editor.setDecorations(decBefore, [new vscode.Range(4,0,4,0), new vscode.Range(5,lines[5].length,5,lines[5].length), new vscode.Range(7,0,7,0)]);
    });
  }
```

- VSCode Version: 1.2.1
- OS Version: Windows 7

Steps to Reproduce:
1.  Create a type script file with the following content

``` javascript
 export class sampleClass  {
        public equipmentTypeList: string[] = ["FAX", "OFFICE PHONE"];
        public pbxEquipmentType = "FAX";
        public spliceRightStripName = "TE"; 
        public cablePairStatusValues: any[] =  
            [       
                { statusText: "Assigned" },
                { statusText: "Faulty" }, 
                { statusText: "Not in Use" },
            ];
        public cablePairStatusValueForAssigned = "Assigned";
        public cablePairStatusValueForFaulty = "Faulty";
        public phoneCircuitType = "Phone";
 }
```
1. The syntax highlighting after line 8 of the code above is not correct.
   Tested for following themes
   Default (Dark)
   Visual studio Dark and
   Visual Studio light
   ![syntaxhighlightpreview](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10986887/16266253/dea44e58-3851-11e6-9b50-cb4963197352.PNG)

Note: if the opening square bracket on line 7 is moved to line 6 then the syntax highlighting is OK.
